    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Way We Live Now Poll</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bob McGeever letter opposes as too serious survey in May 7 special issue on new millennium/</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>You people take yourselves too seriously. You survey 1,003 people, an average of about 20 people per state, a good number of whom refused to answer several of your questions, and draw conclusions about the American public that enable you to fill some 36 pages. This is a waste of time for those of us who look forward to the magazine every week!</p>
        <p>Bob McGeever</p>
        <p>Cameron Park, Calif.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>You people take yourselves too seriously. You survey 1,003 people, an average of about 20 people per state, a good number of whom refused to answer several of your questions, and draw conclusions about the American public that enable you to fill some 36 pages. This is a waste of time for those of us who look forward to the magazine every week!</p>
        <p>Bob McGeever</p>
        <p>Cameron Park, Calif.</p>
      </block>
